'''[[Basketball]] contests at the [[1972 Summer Olympics]]''' took place at [[Rudi-Sedlmayer-Halle]] in [[Munich]], [[Germany]] from August 27 to September 9. This edition of the tournament marked the first time the [[United States men's national basketball team|United States]] did not win a gold medal since the sport's inception into the Olympic Games in 1936, and ended up with the silver instead in a controversial final match against the [[Soviet Union national basketball team|Soviet Union]]. The bronze went to [[Cuba national basketball team|Cuba]], the first and only Olympic medal up to the present day for the nation's basketball team.

